condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Annual work plan for civil works for 2nd year of project implementation onwards | Description :The recipientshall prepare an annual work plan for civil works commencing of the second year of project implementation until project completionsatisfactory to IDA. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Business Plan to carry out Maintenance Policy. | Description :The Recipient shall prepare and adopt a 3-yearbusiness plan to carry out the rural roads maintenance policy. | Due Date :30-Jun-2015

Finance Agreement :Completion of land acquisition actions. | Description :Except as IDA shall otherwise agree, the Recipient shallensure that land acquisition actions under a Sub-project are completed before awarding the contract for civil works under saidSub-project. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Governance and Accountability Action Plan. | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the project is carriedout in accordance with the provisions of the Governance and Accountability Action Plan. | Frequency :SemiAnnual

Finance Agreement :Implementation of Resettlement Action Plan. | Description :The Recipient shall not displace any affected personsunder a Sub-project until and unless the implementation of the Resettlement Action Plan for the Sub-project has been completed. |Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Maintenance Policy. | Description :The Recipient shall adopt a rural roads maintenance policy acceptable to IDA.| Due Date :31-Dec-2012

Finance Agreement :Selection of roads under Sub Component A2. | Description :The Recipient shall select the roads forrehabilitation and periodic maintenance, and for maintenance through PBMC using criteria and methodologies agreed with IDA. |Frequency :Yearly

title.narrative: Increase in maintenance budget needs met for the rural roads
Increase in population living within 2 km of all season upazila and union roads improved under RTIP II in 26 project districts
Rehabilitation and periodic maintenance + Performance Based Maintenance Contract (PBMC) roads.
Increase of upazila and union roads under RPM and PBMC sub-components of RTIP II in good condition (IRI below 7) in 26 project districts (5, 861 km of paved roads)
Business Plan developed on the Maintenance Policy.
LGED implementation of comprehensive IT-based maintenance management system
LGED implementation of Integrated Decision Support System (IDSS).
